body: Hi Jasonroc, My best guess is that and old version of Honeybee is executed in your definition. That's my bad not to update the example files for the new release which I hope to get fixed tomorrow. If you drop Honeybee_Honeybee component from Honeybee tab to canvas and try again the problem should be solved. Is Honeybee itself flying fine on your system? (e.g. what is the output of Honeybee_Honeybee component on your system?). You should see something like this: [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/zbcSW1D04asBVC1fCqZpZOPvDnCXdSDIguknr1rnQGd9MzcclAK3rQvz79hfs3iDM*uVXwT5S8NyOcSNfXYvvtNI-aWVWT8c/HoneybeeMood.png) In case it didn't solve the problem, upload your file here and I will give it a try.
